string 1:
A Mammal Digimon resembling a rabbit, born from 
the fusion of moon observation data. Its large ears 
can recognize sounds from any distance. Although 
timid, Lunamon often gets lonely and easily grows 
attached to others. It uses its special move 
Tearing Shot to concentrate power into the antenna 
on its forehead to shoot a beautiful orb of water at 
the enemy.

A Beast Man Digimon with astounding jumping 
capabilities that likes to toy with its foes using 
speedy movements. Lekismon's nature is as 
ephemeral as the phases of the moon, and its 
appearance is somewhat mystical. It uses its 
special move Moon Night Bomb to hurl hypnotic
water bubbles generated from the Moon Gloves 
on its hands and put the enemy to sleep.

A Rock/Mineral Digimon discovered when 
performing digital analysis of an ancient curse. It 
has forbidden incantations in an archaic script
signifying "plague," "curse" and "evil" inscribed on
its back, apparently meant to safeguard it from
the gas it emits. Approximately 90% of its body is
composed of rock data, and it survives by binding
up its limbs. An emotionless Digimon that doesn't
act unless so ordered.

A mutant Machine Digimon shaped like a gear. 
There are also countless other gears built into its 
body that are constantly turning. If even one gear 
is removed, all of the others stop spinning and 
Hagurumon ceases to function. Hagurumon possesses
the ability to infect foes with a computer virus that
allows it to control them. Thus, Digimon of wicked
intent often seek to exploit Hagurumon's powers.
But since it lacks any sense of self, it has no way
of knowing it's being used for evil. Its special move
is Cog Crusher, which implants a black gear
loaded with a computer virus into its opponent's
body, causing them to go berserk.

A Fire Digimon whose body is cloaked in crimson 
flames. Generated of the Firewall built to defend 
against illegal intrusions from the Internet, this 
Digimon has a violent temperament that reflects 
its blazing appearance and seeks to incinerate
anything it touches. Its flames burn more intensely 
than those of its kindred on File Island, making it
an extremely difficult Digimon to tame. But even if 
tamed, there's no telling when Meramon will turn 
on its master. Meramon uses its special move 
Burning Fist to cause its arms to flare up before 
punching its foe.

A Mythical Beast Digimon with gigantic wings. 
Airdramon is an exceptionally valuable monster,
thought to be near in stature to a god. It specializes
in aerial combat, invoking storms with its roar and
creating colossal whirlwinds by flapping its wings.
Though quite vicious by nature, Airdramon is also
very intelligent. Nevertheless, any average Tamer
would find it nearly impossible to control. Airdramon
beats its huge wings to unleash a cutting vacuum
blade with its special move Spinning Needle.

A wolf-like Beast Digimon with a pale silver pelt. 
Garurumon's fur is said to be as hard as the 
legendary rare metal Mithril, and the blades
extending from its shoulders are sharp enough to 
slice through anything they touch. Possessed of a
physique honed in the frozen tundra and a fierce 
instinct for conflict, Garurumon is feared by other 
Digimon for its predatory agility and unerring 
accuracy in bringing down its prey. However, it's 
also incredibly intelligent and steadfastly loyal to 
any it acknowledges as its leader. Garurumon uses 
its special move Fox Fire to breathe out a stream 
of intense blue flames.

A Ghost Digimon with a cloth draped over it. 
Bakemon is a wicked being born of darkness, and 
is said to instantly destroy the systems of any 
computers it possesses. What lies beneath the 
cloth is a complete mystery, and there are theories 
that the shadow cast under its body is a black hole. 
Bakemon lacks combat power and thus prefers not 
to attack its foes directly. Its special move 
Death Charm casts a powerful curse. Those lacking 
strong mental fortitude die in a matter of seconds 
under its effect.

A star-shaped Digimon discovered by chance in 
planetary analysis software at a space development
center. Starmon is a space warrior with stellar armor,
wearing gloves and boots emblazoned with stars. Its
tattered yellow scarf speaks to the many battles it's
survived, and its eyes burn with fighting spirit. Its
eyes can even be used in a more advanced manner
to hypnotize opponents. This hot-blooded Digimon
has a fierce admiration for the brave Leomon.
Starmon's special move Meteor Shower rains down
small meteors upon the heads of its foes.

A Giant Bird Digimon with a pair of enormous horns 
on its head. Known as the "Great Eagle of the Desert,"
Aquilamon soars through the sky at Mach speed and
can spot distant foes with its keen  eyesight. Its horns
display tremendous force when Aquilamon swoops
down to ram into enemies. While many Bird Digimon
are savagely brutal, Aquilamon values decorum and
obeys those it pledges allegiance to without fail.
It slams into foes from above with its special move
Glide Horn.

A "Commando Dragon" that seeks to become a 
Virus Buster. While Strikedramon still has many 
vestiges of Monodramon, such as the horn jutting 
out of the back of its head, it has so transformed 
its appearance into a Commando-Mode Digimon 
covered in metal plating that it now resembles a 
completely different species. Despite being an 
inherently kindhearted Digimon, should it happen
upon a Virus-attribute type, Strikedramon becomes 
consumed by an instinct to exterminate and 
doesn't stop fighting until its opponent's data has 
been reduced to dust. It uses its special move 
Fang Strike to heat its metal plating to red-hot 
levels, turning itself into a mass of flame and 
tackling the opponent in a fearsome maneuver.

A Dark Digimon possessing strong Dark Side 
Power. Minotarumon's movements are slow, but it 
has an extremely tough hide that leaves it unfazed 
by regular attacks. Its special move Darkside Quake
uses the Demon Arm attached to its left arm to
cause a massive earthquake. The attack sends
shockwaves over a wide area, making escape
impossible no matter how far enemies run.

A mouse-like Digimon that's always filling Sukamon's
head with shady ideas. Chuumon has a solid
friendship with Sukamon (although perhaps
it's only Chuumon that sees things that way).
The relationship started when Chuumon was nearly
caught in a network system trap named "Carnivore,"
only to be rescued by Sukamon, who just happened
to be passing by. Fundamentally a coward,
Chuumon is unrivaled in its slyness and takes
off like a shot at the slightest hint of danger. 
Its special move Cheese Bomb hurls a cheese-shaped
explosive. Anyone who makes the mistake of
eating one of these is in for a nasty surprise.

A Mutant Digimon that DNA Digivolved from 
Stingmon and ExVeemon. A chimera of a dragon 
and an insect, this Digimon is known as the 
"Terrible Bee." While Dinobeemon can't be easily 
classified as either a Dragon or an Insectoid type, 
its insect qualities are quite prominent. Flying 
through the air on its four wings, this Digimon 
tracks its foes unerringly with its compound eyes
before choking the life out of them with harsh 
certainty. Dinobeemon is also exceedingly
barbaric by nature. It uses its special move
Hell Masquerade to perform a "dance of Hell,"
cutting through foes with movements fast
enough to leave afterimages.

An Android Digimon modeled after a feral Digimon 
with predatory instincts that enable it to reliably
bring down prey. Raptordramon boasts an incredibly
tough body as well as uncontrollable savagery, and
so it has been remodeled with pure Chrondigizoid
Metal of considerable weight to restrict its mobility.
Nevertheless, it still possesses exceptional explosive
power and flight capabilities, largely due to the feral
Digimon it used to be prior to remodeling.
Though small, Raptordramon is capable of taking
down even ultra-large Digimon in a single blow if
it can gradually unlock its abilities.
It performs its special move Ambush Crunch by
pouncing on the enemy and biting vitals with its
sharp fangs.

Sangloupmon is a bloodsucking wolf Digimon with 
a noble demeanor. It's one of the oldest species of 
Digimon, said to have survived since the dawn of 
the Digital World. Digimon who have their blood 
sucked by Sangloupmon have all the data drained
from their DigiCores, causing them to perish, as 
they can no longer maintain vital functions. 
Sangloupmon is capable of teleporting to other 
locations instantly by disassembling its own data 
into packets and sending them across the Net. Its 
special move is Sticker Blade, which fires off a 
spray of thousands of minute blades to skewer 
opponents in the blink of an eye.

An Insectoid Digimon affiliated with the mysterious
Royal Base, a secret floating honey base.
While its daily life may differ from that of other
Insectoid Digimon, FunBeemon has a cheery
disposition and is a hard worker of considerable
strength. It always gets along with Vegetation
Digimon like Palmon or Lillymon. The Royal Base
is under constant construction, and Funbeemon's
mission requires it to collect field data such as
flowers or plants a little at a time as building
materials. It's therefore classified as having the
Virus attribute. The base is also guarded by
powerful Digimon that prevent any from drawing
near, so the purpose of the construction remains
a mystery. FunBeemon's special move is Gear
Stinger, an attack that fires off a rapid volley of
tiny, serrated stingers.

A Virus Gatomon with striking black fur. 
BlackGatomon is the quintessential child of evil, 
spendings its days wandering through eerie 
darkness. An extremely rare mutation of Gatomon, 
very few are thought to exist. BlackGatomon is
malicious and prideful and loves picking on the 
weak—all in all a problematic Digimon. As a Dark
Digimon, it generally Digivolves into a Dark Angel 
Digimon. Just like Gatomon, BlackGatomon's 
special move is Lightning Paw.

A small, dinosaur-like Reptile Digimon that has 
developed the ability to walk on two legs. Since it
hasn't fully matured, it still lacks strength, but its 
fierce disposition makes it reckless. Hard, sharp 
claws grow from its hands and feet, and it makes 
full use of them in battle. Agumon shows much 
potential, promising Digivolution into a great and 
powerful Digimon. Its special move is Pepper 
Breath, spitting flames at its foes.

An Android Digimon born from the fusion of the 
data from a portable music player and that of the 
mythical "kappa" river creature. Gawappamon is 
almost always cheerful as it listens to its favorite 
tunes, but it also sometimes weeps if the disc on 
top of its head gets scratched. It uses its special 
move DJ Shooter to spin its disc at high speed 
and launch it at the enemy.

An Android Digimon that wears a shell like a computer
mouse. Kamemon uses its special move Pointer Arrow
to fire an arrow-shaped missile that it guides to strike
the enemy.

A Holy Beast Digimon that's always wrapped around
a holy ammunition cartridge. Kudamon is constantly
building up holy power within the earring on its left 
ear, and the amount it accumulates affects the
course of its next Digivolution. Calm and collected 
by nature, it can assess any situation—even combat
—with accuracy, ensuring the advantage in battle. 
If things ever go south, though, Kudamon enters 
its cartridge to strengthen its defensive position.
Its special move Blinding Ray dazzles the enemy
with a glaring flash emitted from its earring.

A unique Digimon thought to be a subspecies of
Greymon. GeoGreymon sports a deadlier frame
than ever, with the shell on its head as well as its
entire body having developed into living weapons.
It can charge up a Mega Flame in its mouth to
maximize its destructive power and then unleash
it as a Mega Burst.

A Beast Digimon thought to be a subspecies of
sharp-clawed Gazimon. Gaomon specializes in
hit-and-run attacks using agile movements. The
gloves on its hands are apparently to protect its
claws until they grow in properly. Gaomon uses
its powerful legs to spin and unleash its special
move Double Backhand.

A Vegetation Digimon resembling a flower bud,
Lalamon drifts through the sky by rotating the
leaves on its head. Despite its lack of expression,
it has a great deal of charm. Its special move
Seed Blast shoots hard seeds from its mouth with
a surprising degree of accuracy.

A Vegetation Digimon resembling a sunflower. 
Sunflowmon gets a real energy boost when it's 
exposed to sunlight, which makes its attacks more 
powerful. On sunny days, it may even fly around by 
flapping the two leaves growing from its back. Its
special move is Sunshine Beam, which releases 
a blast of sunlight from its petals.

This Beast Digimon is the result of Gaomon's 
physique developing and the claws that were once 
protected by gloves finally growing in properly.
Although GaoGamon is a quadruped, its hind legs 
are strong enough for it to stand like a bear while 
it attacks. GaoGamon unleashes its special move
Spiral Blow to shoot a powerful vortex of wind 
from its mouth in one breath.

An extremely rare Numemon that first discovered
the Platina Mine in the Digital World, taking in those
components to Digivolve. From that point on,
PlatinumNumemon's personality did a complete
about-face as it scraped together any jewelry data
it could find, decorating itself like a nouveau riche.
It's quite the "gorgeous" Digimon, despite its nature.
Outfitting itself with golden wings and jewelry grants
it considerable defense, but its attack power is
middling at best. PlatinumNumemon uses its special
move Platinum Excrement to hurl the dregs
(excrement) produced during the platina refinement
process in rapid succession. It also uses Platinum
Burp to release a putrid belch that saps the enemy's
fighting spirit.

A slug-like Mollusk Digimon. Fond of damp, dark 
environments, Numemon lacks both offensive 
power and intelligence. Any Digimon can become
a Numemon if it isn't raised properly, but perhaps 
it has hidden depths? Then again, even its attacks
are bottom-tier, flinging its own poop to defend 
against enemies.

This Beast Man Digimon is known as the 
"King of Beasts," and also the "Noble Hero." 
Standing out amidst the many savage Digimon 
out there, Leomon possesses both strength of will 
as well as a sense of justice, which it has wielded 
to defeat scores of villains. It has a rival in the
"Digimon Hunter" Ogremon, which devotes itself 
entirely to acts of destruction. Leomon hones its
formidable physique with daily training so that 
it can withstand all attacks, and it kills foes with 
its ultimate technique, the special move Fist of 
the Beast King. From Leomon's waist hangs 
Shishiou-maru, the Beast Sword with a will of 
its own.

A Digimon resembling a kamaitachi—a mythical 
weasel-like creature—with a blade for a tail. This 
tail moves with a will of its own, allowing Reppamon 
to handle even surprise attacks from the rear. That 
will doesn't always line up with Reppamon's, though, 
so this Digimon has been observed quarreling with 
its own tail during battle. Reppamon enjoys combat 
in wooded areas, making good use of its claws and 
tail to climb nimbly among the trees. Thus, one must 
exercise considerable caution when battling Reppamon
in wooded areas. Its special move Rolling Tackle is a
forward-rolling charge.

A Dark Dragon Digimon known as the "Deep 
Crimson Dragon." Having Digivolved into a wilder, 
more ferocious creature, the childishness from 
its time as Guilmon is now gone. Although it's 
a Virus Digimon, Growlmon may become loyal 
depending on how its Tamer raises it, perhaps
even fighting for justice. Its roar is mighty enough 
to shake the ground, and Growlmon uses it as 
an aggressive display to intimidate the enemy
before battle. It has the special move Exhaust 
Flame, which unleashes a powerful blast of fire 
with an explosive roar.

Impmon is a Rookie Digimon that looks like a devil
child. It loves to pull pranks, relishing the thought
of watching its victims struggle. Rumor has it that
whenever Impmon appears, electrical appliances
briefly go haywire, so if your screen ever shakes or
freezes, it might be because Impmon is pulling a
prank. But as much as Impmon delights in mischief
and malice, it's not one to meekly bow down before
the strong. It puts on a brave face and stands up to
them instead. Deep down, it's actually quite lonely.
Impmon's signature move is Summon, which calls
forth fire and ice elementals.

An Angel Digimon with six shining wings and a
body clad in divine white cloth. This being of
absolute goodness is said to bring happiness.
Angemon remains utterly composed in the face
of evil, attacking relentlessly until its foe is
annihilated. Legend has it that Angemon has
often descended at the head of a host of other
Digimon of the same species when the Digital
World was in crisis. It's also said that Devimon,
who was lured to the Dark Side, was originally of
the same species. Angemon's special move is
Heaven's Knuckle, with which it pummels its foe
with a shining fist of gold.

A Holy Knight Digimon and member of the Royal 
Knights, Omnimon was fused from the Virus Busters
WarGreymon and MetalGarurumon through the
will of those who wish for good. Omnimon is
able to draw on the qualities of both Digimon
to the fullest extent under any circumstance,
making it a capable and versatile fighter. Its
left arm is in the shape of WarGreymon, with
a sword and shield, and its right hand takes 
the shape of MetalGarurumon, equipped with 
a cannon and missiles. The cloak on its back 
deploys automatically when it needs to avoid
enemy attacks or to fly. Omnimon's special 
move is Supreme Cannon, fired from the 
MetalGarurumon-shaped cannon on its right 
arm. Omnimon's left arm is equipped with the 
invincible blade, Transcendent Sword.

A Digimon resembling a young dinosaur. Although
Guilmon is still a Rookie Digimon, it possesses a
carnivore's brutality and the great potential as a
fighting species that all Digimon naturally possess
The mark on its abdomen is called a DIgital Hazard,
and is inscribed on any Digimon with the ability to
cause serious damage to computer data. Still, if
used for the sake of peace, this ability could
potentially make this Digimon a guardian of the
Digital World. Guilmon can use its signature move
Rock Breaker to destroy even stone with its rugged
front claws.

An extremely unusual Insectoid Digimon with a 
humanoid shape. Stingmon possesses both the 
hard exoskeleton and the simple movements
characteristic of Insectoid Digimon. Excelling 
as an assassin, it prides itself on attacks that 
target vitals with agile movements and precise 
judgment, silencing the enemy with a single 
strike. Stingmon possesses a calm, cool and 
highly intelligent personality. It uses its fearsome
special move Spiking Strike to skewer foes with 
the spikes on its arms.

A Digimon brimming with curiosity who loves to 
pull pranks. Gatomon may be small, but it's still 
a rare Sacred Digimon whose appearance belies 
its true power. It wears its Holy Ring on its tail, 
proving that it's a Holy Digimon, although it will 
lose some of its power if it ever loses this ring. 
Besides the Holy Ring, to protect itself, Gatomon 
also wears gloves with long, sharp claws copied
from the data of SaberLeomon. Gatomon's 
special move Lightning Paw uses its claws to 
attack the opponent.

A Dark Angel Digimon clothed in jet-black garb.
Devimon was once a radiant Digimon of the Angemon
species, but it became a Dark Angel when it fell into
the distorted space of the Digital World known as the
Dark Area. The prominent Mark of Evil on its chest is
proof of this. Though it has a cunning and malevolent
personality, Devimon is also extremely intelligent.
It's said that any who stare into its glowing red eyes fall
victim to its mind control and become subject to its
whims. Devimon's special move is Death Claw, which
uses its two extendable arms to pierce its opponent.

A Mammal Digimon known for its large ears. Patamon
can use these to fly, but since it can only do so at
a little over 0.5 mph, its its walking speed is said
to be considerably faster. Even so, watching it
struggle to fly is an endearing sight, making it very
popular (although Patamon itself doesn't appreciate
such sentiment). Patamon is extremely obedient and
very good about doing what it's told. It can also use
its hidden holy power without a Holy Ring—a sign
that it's descended from an Ancient species of
Digimon. Patamon's special move is Air Shot, taking
a deep breath and then releasing a powerful blast
of air.

A small Digimon resembling a bat. DemiDevimon
serves as a familiar to higher-level Digimon like
Devimon and Myotismon. Despite its low status,
it's rumored to have been responsible for tempting
Devimon, once an Angel Digimon, over to the
Dark Side. What DemiDevimon lacks in attack
power, it makes up for in malicious cunning,
and it's always causing trouble somewhere.
Fond of darkness and typically in the company
of higher-level Digimon, it's rare to see it by
itself. DemiDevimon's special move is Demi Darts,
which throws giant syringes at the enemy to
drain its blood.

A brutal Beast Man Digimon formed when Lopmon
underwent Dark Digivolution due to anger and
hatred. Wendigomon isn't completely evil, and the
kindness it had as Lopmon still resides somewhere
deep in its heart. But the power of its rage overrides
this kindness, making Wendigomon devote itself
completely to destruction. In addition to its raw
power, Wendigomon has the ability to manipulate
time and space, and is able to warp by passing
through other dimensions as well as create
subdimensions of its own. Its special move is
Howling Destroyer, which creates a shockwave
capable of shattering even boulders.

A martial artist Digimon discovered in the hinterland
of a mountainous Chinese province. 
Turuiemon has wandered the world in pursuit of 
its longstanding foes—viruses that exploit e-mail 
for malicious aims. It's blessed with exceptional
potential as a martial artist, though it has yet to 
develop its skills. Turuiemon is a practitioner of
Togaken, a fighting style of its own creation.
Its special move is Gauntlet Claw, which involves
a series of blows made with the Rabbit-Horned
Iron Claws on both hands. This combo attack
capitalizes on its rabbit-like agility and powerful
high leaps.

A Crustacean Digimon that attached metal data that
had been dissolved into the Net Ocean to its body,
dramatically increasing its combat capability.
Crabmon attacks with the giant blades on its left
pincer and the powerful grip of its right pincer.
For defense, it relies on its spiny shell to damage
attackers, and is utterly self-confident in battle.
Crabmon is fully aware of the weak points of its
joints and underbelly, and thus rarely leaves them
exposed. It enjoys trapping its opponents, and is
something of a prankster. Crabmon's special move
is Scissors Execution, which launches its sharp
left pincer right for its adversary's throat.

A Digimon resembling a troublesome imp that
loves mischief. Crafty creatures devoid of courage,
Goblimon always move in groups, hiding in the
shadows of trees or buildings while waiting in
ambush. But if the situation goes south, they
scatter in all directions, fleeing at full speed.
Their intelligence, on the other hand, is above
average for Rookie Digimon. Goblimon's special
move is Goblin Strike, which hurls fireballs at
Mach speed.

Because of the antiquated interface on its forehead,
this Beast Digimon is presumed to be an experimental
"Prototype Digimon" from the time before Digimon
were discovered. The personality characteristic of the
Combat Species is particularly apparent in Dorumon.
It has a strong instinct for battle, biting and roaring
at anything and everything, though it apparently feels
a sense of attachment to something after biting it.
The strong life force data of the legendary "dragon"
was found to have been hidden in the deepest part
of its DigiCore during an experiment, and Dorumon
apparently has the potential to grow into a mighty
Digimon. Dorumon's special move is Metal Cannon,
which fires an iron ball from its mouth.

A subspecies of Numemon whose entire body glitters 
gold, having incorporated data from gold mines into 
itself. GoldNumemon's special move is Goldurian Rush,
by which it hurls a stream of golden poop.

A new type of Digimon only recently discovered.
Veemon is a surviving member of a species that
once thrived in the dawn of the Digital World.
This allows it to use Digi-Eggs to perform a type of
pseudo-Digivolution known as Armor Digivolution.
Of all its peers, Veemon is one of the best
Combat Species. It possesses hidden power, and
uses Armor Digivolution to bring out its explosive
abilities. Though a troublemaker and a prankster by
nature, Veemon also has a strong sense of justice.
Its special move is Veemon Headbutt, which knocks
down foes with a powerful blow with the top of its head.

Huckmon went through strict training, refining an 
unparalleled combat sense and achieving mental, 
technical and physical strength in this form.
BaoHuckmon continues to train while aiming for 
even greater heights, accumulating combat 
experience through countless battles against
strong foes. The more this combat expert fights, 
the more it evolves. BaoHuckmon's desire to 
become a Royal Knight has only increased as it's
grown. It doesn't allow others to determine its 
best course of action, believing it should observe 
and decide on an approach for itself. 
With its special move Fif Cross, BaoHuckmon
cleaves its opponent with its sharp claws.

An Ancient Fish Digimon with tough skin and 
enormous claws. This Digimon is discovered in 
the Net Ocean whenever computer networks
destroyed by malicious hackers are repaired.
Coelamon's body composition is very primitive, 
with fins developed into limbs. Based on these 
facts, it's thought that primordial Digimon born 
in the Net Ocean underwent various evolutions in 
order to come onto land, growing more numerous 
and differentiating into various types in the 
process. Coelamon's special move is Fossil Bite, 
which attacks enemies with its massive claws.

A Beast Digimon born through the fusion of data 
obtained by observing the sun. Coronamon has a 
strong sense of justice and a pure, simple-minded
personality. Its special move is Corona Flame, which
converts all of the stamina in its body into flame
power to shoot a fiery missile at the enemy from its 
forehead.

A Beast Digimon known as the "Soaring Lion." 
Firamon is a helpful leader among Digimon that 
protects certain ruins in the Digital World. Its
special move is Flame Dive, with which it envelops
its body in flames and dive-bombs the enemy
from the skies above.

A full-fledged Reptile Digimon, despite being covered
in fur. Gabumon is an extremely shy, timid creature
who always gathers up data left behind by
Garurumon to wear like a pelt. Garurumon's pelt
also serves to protect Gabumon, since other
Digimon fear the original owner. Gabumon's personality
makes a complete about-face when it wears the
pelt. Its special move is Blue Blaster.

A Digimon with power over water, it bears the might 
of the Ten Legendary Warriors. Lanamon has a sharp
intuition and an changeable mood, due perhaps to 
the fact that it used to operate mainly in the ocean 
area of a weather forecasting system. Its emotions 
are tempestuous, acting like a lovely young lady 
when in a good mood, and crying like a hysterical
baby when it gets upset. Lanamon uses few direct 
attacks in battle, relying instead on manipulated 
rain or other indirect methods of fighting. That 
being said, its battle strength swells during surges 
of emotion, with its combat prowess growing 
unfathomably strong when crying. Lanamon's 
special move is Rain Stream, which focuses 
torrential rain to crush the enemy.

A Digimon with power over water, it bears the might 
of the Ten Legendary Warriors. Half humanoid and 
half beast, Calmaramon can spin its tentacles at 
high speed for offense, or gather them together 
into a defensive wall, making for a versatile tool in 
combat. If it can't finish an opponent with its 
tentacles, Calmaramon withdraws into its mantle, 
increasing the power of its attacks as it takes on 
the form of a giant squid. This mantle is even more 
resilient than its tentacles, rendering external 
physical attacks against it harmless. Though 
Calmaramon is more accustomed to the seas and 
skies, it can skillfully maneuver its ten tentacles to 
move around on land like a giant hermit crab as well. 
Much like a witch, it's crafty and quick to anger. 
Its special move is Titanic Charge, which spins
its hardened mantle to drill into foes.

A Deity Digimon with the upper body of a human 
and the lower body of a mountain goat. Aegiomon
is usually affiliated with the same musical troupe
as Sirenmon, reveling in the music by playing the
Syrinx flute hanging from his waist. He loves peace,
and although he dislikes fighting, an unknown
quantity of power dwells within him, and he
demonstrates exceptional combat prowess when
fighting to protect something he cares about.
Aegiomon plays Attract Echo on his Syrinx to draw
the listener's attention, stealing its sense of self and
making it unable to see anything but Aegiomon as it
remains fixated on the tune. This gives other Digimon
the chance to escape or pursue said listener.
Aegiomon's special move is Stun Beat Blow, which
strikes the opponent and discharges the electricity
in Aegiomon's body through his arms, numbing the
enemy's nerves and rendering it unable to move.

Because of the antiquated interface on its forehead,
this Beast Digimon is presumed to be an experimental
"Prototype Digimon" from the time before Digimon were
discovered. Ryudamon is covered in Japanese-style
armor that boasts high defense, yet its movements are
quite nimble, allowing it to jump in and fight at brazenly
close range. The more it fights, the more it cultivates
combat prowess. Ryudamon possesses gallantry, a
samurai spirit and a soul that renders it unafraid of
powerful enemy Digimon. The data hidden within
the deepest part of its DigiCore during the experiment
contains such fierce combat data as warlords and
dragons from Japanese mythology, and Ryudamon
is thought to possess the potential to grow into a
mighty Digimon. Its special move is Iai Blade, with
which it leaps up to the opponent to fire an iron
blade from its mouth at point-blank range.

A Beast Dragon Digimon with sturdy Japanese-style
armor covering its whole body. Ginryumon is lighter
than it appears, drifting gracefully through the air and
fighting while parrying enemy attacks with its smooth
and extremely tough armor. It has the courage to fend
off enemy attacks with its own body, and the insight to
accurately perceive said attacks right before they land.
Ginryumon specializes in attacks with outstanding
penetrative ability, and is unflinching in the face of any
enemy Digimon. Because of the antiquated interface
on its forehead, this Digimon is presumed to be the
Digivolution of an experimental "Prototype Digimon."
Ginryumon's special move is Metal Armor Blade,
which impales its foe with an iron lance launched
from its mouth.

Dracomon is a Dragon Digimon of an old bloodline
said to trace back to the progenitor of all Dramon-
species Digimon. It possesses physical capabilities
difficult to even imagine given its small size, with
its speed and power ranking among the very best
of all Rookie Digimon. Though extremely fierce by
nature, it also has a softer side it only shows to
those it deems worthy of its trust. Despite having
wings, they're not fully developed, so Dracomon is
unable to fly. One of its other defining characteristics
is its drive to collect "shiny things,"and it has an
odd attachment to gems and certain types of metal.
If it's particularly fond of some shiny object, it
will eat it. Its special move is Baby Breath, which
it uses to breathe out a blast of hot air.

Coredramon with green bodies are said to have 
Digivolved from Dracomon that ate lots of Green 
Malachite, a precious gem mined from forest
regions thickly wooded with trees over 100 years
old. Coredramon (Green) isn't skilled at flying,
but has highly-developed leg muscles, and is
capable of running at speeds seemingly impossible 
for a creature of its size. Its special move is Green 
Flare Breath, with which it breathes out scorching 
green flames. Green Flare Breath penetrates deep
beneath surface texture data to damage the enemy's
DigiCore directly.

Coredramon with blue bodies are said to have
Digivolved from Dracomon that ate lots of Blue
Diamante, a precious gem that can only be mined
from mountainous regions with the highest of
peaks. Coredramon (Blue) has developed strong
wings to survive amid the steep slopes, and is
capable of flying at great speed. Its special move
is Blue Flare Breath, with which it breathes out
scorching blue flames. Blue Flare Breath breaks
down a foe's surface texture data, leaving the
DigiCore of a Digimon hit by this move exposed
and open to attack.

A Reptile Digimon that aims to become the greatest
swordsman of the Digimon world. Kotemon is a hard
worker that silently endeavors to train in unseen areas.
It never removes its face protector, so its bare face
is a total mystery. Although Kotemon is cowardly
and prone to crying, it cares for its friends deeply
and has a strong sense of justice, and occasionally
even displays a stalwart side. With its special move
Hothead, it engulfs its bamboo sword in flames
before aiming for the head of its foe.

An armored warrior Digimon that was once the data 
of a video game protagonist, but then Digivolved
after being infected by a computer virus. Numerous 
battles with other Digimon have rendered Musyamon's
appearance into that of a pathetic battlefield deserter, 
but that's only proof of its fearsome battle prowess 
and vitality. A savage warrior that's survived endless 
battles—that's Musyamon in a nutshell. The demon
sword Shiratori-maru in its right hand is engraved with 
a forbidden spell that absorbs the life force of those it 
cuts, and is said to only grow sharper with every 
thousand Digimon it slashes down. Musyamon also 
has a special move called Kirisute Gomen that it 
unleashes from its Shiratori-maru. One day, it will
settle things with Leomon, crossing its beloved blade 
with Leomon's.

Originally a Virus-attribute type, Dobermon is a 
Hunter Digimon that changed into a Vaccine type 
as a result of mutation. Like Snimon, however, it 
remains quite vicious despite its Vaccine status, 
living only to hunt down Virus Digimon. Dobermon 
is beyond the control of the average Tamer. Its 
special move is Grau Lärm, with which it lets out a
howl that prevents its opponents from using their 
abilities.

A Composite Digimon fused from three Digimon. Each 
existed as a separate Digimon, but a computer ran 
amok after getting hit by a powerful electromagnetic 
storm, bugging out and fusing them together into
Deltamon. A Digimon with three heads and two tails, 
it specializes in three-stage attacks utilizing these
physical features, making it capable of taking on 
three Digimon at once. Still, each part of it was once 
a fiendish Digimon, so while they share a mindset 
for destruction, they have no spirit of cooperation, 
and are usually on bad terms. Deltamon uses its 
special move Triple Forces to unleash energy from 
all three mouths in a single blast.

A Digimon that resembles a "baku," a being in
Japanese folklore that eats dreams. Believed to
have been born from a medical computer that
monitors brainwaves, Tapirmon seems to feed on
human REM sleep data. In the latest round of
research, it was also found to possess the ability
to erase nightmares and computer viruses. Since
it can also return those nightmares and viruses to
a benign state, it's believed to be a Holy Digimon.
The Holy Ring it wears on one of its forelegs seems
likely related to both its special abilities and Holy
nature. Tapirmon's special move is Nightmare
Syndrome, which releases all of the nightmares it
absorbed at once to terrify its adversaries. This is
the same special move as that of the Perfect
Digimon, Digitamamon, but how the two might be
related remains a mystery.

A Beast Digimon resembling a small bear, wearing
its trademark backwards cap. Although timid at
times, Bearmon gets along well with other Digimon,
and even possesses uncommon pluck and stamina.
Once a battle starts, it continues to fight no matter
how many hits it takes, making for a reliable ally.
The ability for melee fighting it possesses is so
strong that it needs to wrap its fists with leather
belts so it won't injure itself with the destructive
power of its punches. With its special move Bear
Fist, Bearmon leaps at its opponent's chest to
drive home a full-force blow.

Grizzlymon is a Beast Digimon that might seem
ferocious thanks to its large frame, not to mention
its deadly claws and fangs, but it has the honest
and straightforward spirit of a true martial artist.
It has the combat sense to match, too, relying not
only on attacks but moving with a speed that belies
its great bulk to avoid and deflect enemy strikes as
well. Grizzlymon never starts a fight, but when
angered it will draw itself up onto its hind legs
and lash out with its heavyweight bear claws,
"Kumazume." Grizzlymon's strength is such that
just with this one strike it can critically injure most
Digimon. Apparently, WaruMonzaemon wears its
Bear Claw in imitation of this attack. Grizzlymon's
greatest special move, Maul Attack, turns the
force of an enemy's move against it, striking
where it's vulnerable to defeat it in a single blow.

A Mollusk Digimon discovered in a virus that a 
malicious hacker used when trying to crash a rival's
computer. Octomon is an obsessive collector,
sporting claws at the ends of its tentacles that it 
obtained from Devidramon's data, and covering
itself in Digi-Treasure that it scavenged from the 
depths of the Net Ocean. Many Fujitsumon, which 
are a small type of shellfish Digimon, have attached
themselves to the pot that Octomon wears on its
head. These Fujitsumon have highly-developed
senses, and it's believed that they are part of a
symbiotic relationship with Octomon, warning it
when they sense danger. Octomon's special move,
Spurting Ink, fires out a blast of highly-poisonous
ink.

A super-small Machine Digimon with red eyes that 
act as photosensors. Choromon's constant restless
movements make it seem very cute, but they're
just because of its simple programming making it
react to bright light. In dark places, it can't move at
all. For reasons unknown, it discharges electricity
from the tip of its tail when it's in a good mood. It
uses its move Jamming Powder to emit metal
particles and temporarily confuse its enemy's AI. It
then takes advantage of this temporary confusion
to flee.

A small, In-Training Digimon wearing a metal helmet.
The two horns on the helmet contain antennae that 
can transmit all sorts of radio waves or sounds. 
Kapurimon has batlike traits, emitting ultrasonic 
waves from its mouth and recognizing objects ahead
of it from the rebounding waves, instead of relying
on its weak eyesight. This allows it to remain active 
no matter what time of day or night it is. Kapurimon 
uses its special move Howling Hertz to make its two 
horns resonate. Anyone hit by this attack has their 
hearing paralyzed, even large Digimon.

The prototypical Insectoid Digimon, Tentomon has 
a hard carapace but a low level of aggression.
Tentomon has one claw on each of its forelegs, and
four claws on its middle and hind legs. Its middle
legs in particular are highly dexterous, similar to
human hands. Though other Insectoid Digimon of
Tentomon's Digivolution level are consumed by a
strong fighting spirit, Tentomon retains a love and
appreciation for nature at this stage. Exhibiting a
fondness for relaxation, Tentomon stops to smell
flowers and nap in the shade of trees. Even so, it
does have the special move Super Shocker, which
involves using its wings to shoot out amplified
bolts of static electricity.

Even for a newly-discovered Digimon, Kabuterimon
is highly unusual. Though it's unclear how it came
to be an Insectoid type, it's understood to have
the power of an ant and the defense system of a
beetle. As you would expect from an insect, it only
thinks about survival, and has no other intelligence
whatsoever. Hostile toward Virus Digimon, Kabuterimon
attacks on sight without mercy. Its head is made
of metal, granting it impregnable defense. Its special
move is Electro Shocker.

A Baby Bird Digimon with arm-like wings. Biyomon
can use these to dexterously grip objects, though
this limits its ability to fly. It spends most of its
time on the ground, but can escape into the air
when danger draws near. Since it's similar in flying
ability to Patamon, Biyomon sees Patamon as a
rival. Biyomon's dream is to one day Digivolve into
Birdramon and fly freely through the sky. Its
nightmare is becoming Kokatorimon, who can't
fly at all. Possessed of an inquisitive mind, it likes
to peck at the sprout growing from Tanemon's
head. Biyomon's special move is Spiral Twister, an
attack of spectral flames.

A Giant Bird Digimon wreathed in blazing flames. 
Like Meramon, whose body is also shrouded in 
crimson flames, Birdramon is a Digimon formed 
from the Internet's defensive Firewall. Birdramon 
flies through the sky using its massive wings. 
Despite not having a combative nature, Birdramon 
nevertheless launches frenzied counterattacks in 
the face of enemy assaults. Birdramon's special 
move is Meteor Wing, flapping its wings to send 
feathers shooting down like meteors.

A nasty Digimon shaped like a glittering piece of
golden poop. Sukamon was born from the accumulation
and mutation of data scraps thrown away in the trash
can of a computer desktop. It loves dark places, and
being a pile of scrap data, it's just as disliked by other
Digimon as Numemon. Sukamon's intelligence and
attack power are both nonexistent. Its small rodent
partner Chuumon can't fight, but is as crafty as they
come, and always entices Sukamon into doing
wicked deeds.

A Carnivorous Vegetation Digimon with long vines
and a gaping maw. This fiendish brute emits a sweet
smell from its mouth to lure in smaller Digimon,
then ensnares them with its long,  tentacle-like vines.
Still, Vegiemon lacks any offensive power, making it no
match for large-scale Digimon. When it grows, it will 
flower and bear fruit.

A Slime Digimon covered entirely in a tough material
called Mithril Hair. Dodomon exhibits an aggressive 
nature right from birth, and even though its fangs
haven't grown in yet, it likes to threaten foes by 
opening wide and pretending to bite them. Because 
of this behavior, these Digimon are often taken out 
by others, making Dodomon quite rare. When an 
enemy approaches, Dodomon attacks by shooting 
Little Iron Beads from its mouth.

A newborn Digital Monster. Dark peach fuzz covers 
the surface of Botamon's slimy body. This new 
addition to the Digital World can't fight, but it can 
spout Acid Bubbles from its mouth in an attempt
to threaten foes.

This Digimon baby uses its translucent body to float
along the Net Ocean like a jellyfish. Possessing the 
most primitive structural makeup of any Digimon
discovered to date, it garners attention from Digital 
World anthropologists and Digimon fanatics alike. 
They hail it as a "missing link," potentially capable of
unlocking the mystery behind Digimon generation. 
To protect itself from foes, Poyomon shoots 
Acid Bubbles from its mouth.

A Digimon that fuses the data of small pet animals 
such as cats and dogs. Wanyamon is unexpectedly 
swift, so caution is warranted to prevent its escape. 
Even so, it gets quite attached if you fawn over it like
a pet. Its special move is Smile Fang, going suddenly 
from an innocent-looking pose to a surprise chomp 
attack.

A small Digimon whose body has grown a size bigger,
its peach fuzz having fallen off. Koromon can move
around vigorously, but combat is still beyond its
capabilities. It blows Bubbles from its mouth to 
intimidate foes.

A small Digimon with four limbs growing out of the
bottom of its body (head?). These limbs, which are
highly unusual on an In-Training Digimon, give 
Tokomon a unique and extremely cute look. 
However, that cuteness can be deceptive, and 
anyone who reaches out to pet Tokomon may be
in for a surprise as it quickly opens its mouth and 
bites down with its rows of sharp teeth. Tokomon 
has an innocent personality, though, and doesn't 
mean any real harm.

A Dinosaur Digimon with skin hardened into a
protective carapace around its skull. Aggressive
by nature, Greymon uses its sharp claws and
colossal horns as lethal weapons. Taming it earns
you an intelligent ally of unmatched strength. Its
special move is Mega Flame, with which it shoots
searing flames from its mouth, incinerating all.

A Machine Digimon that protects computer network
firewalls. Guardromon used to fight off anyone
attempting to breach a firewall alongside
"Net Keeper" Giromon, until malicious hackers
infected it with a virus to make use of its impregnable
defensive abilities. These hackers now use
Guardromon to protect themselves from a certain
Vaccine justice group. Since Guardromon's basic
programming only involves commands to defend,
it has no problem repelling invaders regardless of
its new role. It uses its special move Destruction
Grenade to pursue invaders to the ends of the
earth and destroy them.

A Sea Beast Digimon that can move on land and
that's covered in temperature-regulating fur. This
short, white fur grows longer and turns brown as
Gomamon ages. A busybody and a troublemaker,
Gomamon loves to get involved in every situation.
The streak of red fur running from its head down
its back moves in accordance with its mood, bristling
when Gomamon is angry. Its claws are sharp
enough to cut through solid ice with ease, and
anyone who underestimates Gomamon is in for a
rude awakening. Its special move is Marching Fishes,
with which Gomamon commands a loyal squad of
small fish to attack.

A Sea Beast Digimon discovered in a computer at
an arctic research facility. Ikkakumon's thick pelt
and sturdy body are made to withstand polar
temperatures. The sharp horn growing from its
head is made of Mithril, a rare metal, and the skin
beneath its pelt is just as hard. Ikkakumon's clawed
limbs are capable of emitting blistering heat at will.
As a result, Ikkakumon can always maintain a firm
foothold when walking on ice, even if unable to
move quickly. In combat, Ikkakumon will threaten
opponents with a bold roar, much like a lion's.
Its special move is Harpoon Torpedo, with which it
fires the horn on its head at the enemy, as the horn
can be regrown.

An Aquatic Digimon with a serpentine body. 
When attacked, Seadramon will wrap its long body 
around the enemy and squeeze them until they 
suffocate. Fundamentally lacking any kind of 
intelligence, Seadramon swims through the Net 
Ocean wherever its instincts take it. Its special 
move is Ice Blast, with which it breathes out from 
its mouth at absolute zero, instantly freezing the 
water and blasting it at its opponent.

A Vegetation Digimon with a tropical flower growing
on its head. Though it Digivolved from Tanemon
in a reptilian fashion, it's a rare type of Digimon
classified as a Vegetation Digimon based on its
appearance and characteristics. During the day,
Palmon opens its flower and leaf-like appendages
to enable photosynthesis. Its root-like feet are
usually buried in the ground absorbing nutrients,
but it can also use them to walk. The flower on
Palmon's head gives off a sweet scent when it's
happy or enjoying itself and a foul stench when
it's angry or feels threatened. The latter is so bad
it can send even larger Digimon running. Palmon's
special move is Poison Ivy, with which it entangles
its foe in highly poisonous vines. Anything hit by
this attack is paralyzed.

A Vegetation Digimon resembling a giant cactus. 
Its ability to store nutrient data inside its body 
allows it to survive for extended periods even in 
barren desert regions. As is obvious from its 
facial expression, it's usually impossible to tell 
what Togemon is thinking, since it spends most 
days staring blankly into space. But if provoked 
enough, its demeanor becomes violent and 
unhinged. Togemon's special move is Needle
Spray, with which it hardens the needles on its 
fists and unleashes a flurry of punches.

Salamon is a young, Sacred-species Digimon with
distinctive floppy ears. Since it's still a child, it isn't
able to make full use of its holy powers, and has
yet to realize its destiny. As a result, its nature is
fundamentally unstable, and it's capable of becoming
either good or evil. There will likely come a day,
however, when Salamon will awaken to its destiny
as one of the Virus Busters. After all, it was born a
sacred Digimon. Salamon is also an experimental
Digimon created by Digimon researchers, and since
it was modeled after a human pet, it looks a great
deal like a real animal. Its special move Puppy Howl
involves letting out a supersonic screech that can
paralyze foes.

A Digimon that looks like an ancient dinosaur that 
existed in the prehistoric world. Tyrannomon mows
down everything with its two powerful arms and 
massive tail. It possesses intelligence and a docile
personality, however, and is easy to tame. This makes
Tyrannomon a hot commodity among beginning 
Tamers, many of whom raise theirs with care. One 
could say it represents what Digimon are all about. 
It uses its special move Fire Breath to exhale flames 
the same color as its deep crimson body.

A Mythical Dragon Digimon that gained Veemon's 
original power and Digivolved to Champion. 
ExVeemon is the pure breed of Veedramon, which 
is said to be a derivative species. Attacks with its 
developed arm and leg strength are capable of
shattering a mountain of boulders without a trace. 
It's feared for this destructive power, but in truth it
has a strong sense of justice, and doesn't use its 
might recklessly. ExVeemon's special move Vee 
Laser fires an energy beam from the X-shaped 
mark on its chest.

An Insectoid Digimon with giant pincers on its head. 
Like Kabuterimon, Kuwagamon possesses combat 
abilities far surpassing those of its kin inhabiting 
File Island. While Kuwagamon enjoys the protection
of its strength and sturdy shell, it uses the power of 
its pincers to squeeze the life out of any foe it catches.
It has a completely hostile relationship with the
Vaccine-attribute Kabuterimon. It can use its
special move Scissor Claw to easily cut through
tough objects.

A Digimon shaped like a hermit crab inhabiting the 
depths of the Net Ocean. Shellmon has a turtle-like
appearance when inside its shell, but its body is 
actually soft like a mollusk. Its body gets bigger and
bigger as it develops, and it switches dwellings each 
time until it's the size of a small mountain. Also, 
Shellmon has the custom of settling into anything it 
can push its whole body into. Its low intelligence and 
belligerent nature mean that anyone who encounters 
it needs to stay on guard. Its special move Hydro 
Blaster fires liquid at high pressure.

An Armored Dragon Digimon with a rhinoceros-like 
horn growing from its snout. When fully grown, this 
horn measures half of Monochromon's body length.
The hard substance that covers its horns and half
its body is as hard as diamond. They say there's
nothing its horn can't pierce. Monochromon is known
to excel at both offense and defense. Although it's
herbivorous and comparatively docile, once it's
angered, it will unleash fearsome counterattacks
with its tank-like body. Its special move Volcanic Strike
is a powerful flame projectile.

An Ice-Snow Digimon whose body is covered in 
snow and ice crystals. In spite of its chilly 
appearance, Frigimon actually has a warm and 
gentle personality. This Digimon calms the hearts 
of those who observe it through its sweet gestures 
and calm movements. Frigimon itself hates the idea 
of fighting, and is ill-suited to other Digimon who 
enjoy combat—Meramon in particular. It unleashes 
its special move Sub-Zero Ice Punch from its sizable 
frame.

A hairy Rare Animal Digimon covered in a thick 
white coat. It lives in remote snowy regions, making
sightings quite rare. In spite of the various reports
of Mojyamon encounters, no evidence has 
confirmed its existence, and so for a long time this 
Digimon has been considered to be a mere fantasy. 
Mojyamon is a gentle creature that never shows 
any hostility, but even so, it treats its den and 
territory as sacred grounds, and doesn't forgive
any who invade its holy land. It hurls a massive 
icicle formed instantly from water in the atmosphere 
with its special move Icicle Rod.

A half-human, half-beast Digimon resembling 
a centaur. Centarumon's body is protected by a 
sturdy substance emitted from inside its body, 
and its right arm is fused with its weapon. It blows 
highly concentrated gas from the ducts sticking 
out of its back to move around at near-sonic 
speeds. It excels in attack, defense and speed.
Pride means everything to Centarumon, and it 
hates being ordered or bound by anything with a 
passion. Its special move Hunting Cannon is fired
from the cannon fused to its right arm. This attack 
is almost impossible to evade, but it consumes 
massive amounts of energy, so Centarumon
avoids battles as much as it can.

A Digimon that moves through the earth at high 
speeds with the giant drill on its nose. Drimogemon 
stays deep in the ground, so only a rare few ever 
meet it. It's docile and easily embarrassed, yet it 
enjoys a good prank, often taking Garurumon's
favorite bone it buried in the ground and hiding it 
someplace else. Its special move Drill Spin attacks 
foes with its giant drill.

An Ultimate Digimon that has the appearance of a 
Digi-Egg and is the alpha and omega of all Digimon.
Digitamamon is the apex of Digivolution, and 
supposedly Digivolves not from a normal Digimon,
but only by fusing with data from another dimension. 
Its egg-shaped exoskeleton renders all attacks
useless. Its special move Nightmare Syndrome is a 
ball of darkness.

An unidentified Digimon that invaded from an 
other-dimensional Digital World. Nanimon went by 
the nickname of "Oyaji" in the other dimension, and 
was kept as a digital pet. It loves alcohol and violence, 
but once it invaded this Digital World (the details of
which are still fuzzy), it Digivolved into an active 
creature. Inspired by the survival-of-the-fittest nature 
of the Digital World, it threw itself into battle. Its true 
power remains unknown. That being said, Nanimon
has made it through many battles and evolved into its
supreme form.

A high-level Wizard Digimon from the Digital World
of another dimension. In its home Digital World of
Witchelny, it mastered the magics of fire and earth
(advanced programming languages) and aims to
become a great mage, but has first come to the
Digimon World for training. Wizardmon is a little
mischievous but also shy and always keeps its
face hidden. Its special move is Thunder Cloud,
which conjures up a storm cloud to launch a
powerful lightning attack.

This Slime Digimon looks like a mere bit of  sea-green
froth at first glance, but it's actually a totally
autonomous creature with a plethora of expressions.
Pabumon's delicate surface means it  has practically
no defense or prowess in combat.  It creates infinite
tiny foam clones from the  pacifier-like object in its
mouth. This ability was originally used to develop
computer viruses, but Pabumon's lack of life force
made for poor implementation. Life is fleeting for this
adorable Digimon baby. It uses Adhesive Bubble Blow
to release bubbles from its body to bind enemies,
giving Pabumon a chance to escape.

A soft-bodied Digimon with highly elastic skin, 
Motimon uses the protrusions beneath its body to
waggle its way around. The name "Motimon" comes
from its resemblance to a mochi rice cake when it 
puffs up its body in excitement. Despite its appearance,
Motimon possesses a surprisingly high degree of
intelligence, and so is believed to have developed
from a computer's dictionary feature. Capable of
understanding human language, Motimon can
occasionally be seen altering the shape of its
body in an effort at communication. Motimon uses
its mochi-like Elastic Bubbles to restrict opponents'
movement.

An Amphibian Digimon that walks on four legs.
Betamon is a docile Digimon with a mild
temperament, although it doesn't hesitate to
unleash its special move Electric Shock when
angered, attacking its enemies with over a
million volts of electric current.

Lucemon is an Angel Digimon resembling a child,
said to have descended from on high long ago in
the Ancient Digital World. It appeared in a time of
chaos, and is said to have ushered in a new era of
peace and order. However, due to Lucemon's
subsequent rebellion, the world was then plunged
into a long, dark age. Despite having the appearance
of a child, Lucemon is wiser and more powerful
than an Ultimate Digimon. It's said that in the
modern era, Lucemon's abilities have been passed
down to and divided among the Three Celestials
Lucemon's special move is Grand Cross, which
fires a collection of ten super-heated spheres
of light arranged into the shape of a cross as if
they were planets in alignment. This attack is
even more destructive than Seraphimon's special
move Strike of the Seven Stars.

A Beast Man Digimon with the appearance of a
golden fox. The relationship Renamon has with
humans is directly apparent, and its In-Training
form can Digivolve into a Digimon of high
intelligence if raised properly. Calm and
collected at all times, it trains in order to keep
its cool in any situation. Renamon's tall, slender
form stands out among Rookie Digimon, and it
prefers the speed of its many techniques over
power when it comes to fighting the enemy. Its
special move Diamond Storm hurls razor-sharp
wood chips at the enemy.

A Larva Digimon with a timid, cowardly personality.
Wormmon is a descendant of the same ancient
species as Veemon, so it can perform a special
Armor Digivolution. Exceedingly weak on its own,
Wormmon stands little chance against larger
Digimon. But with the power of the Digi-Eggs, it
can Armor Digivolve and display incredible power.
Like a larva maturing into an adult, Wormmon will
one day Digivolve into a Champion of great might.
This Digimon is the very embodiment of future
potential. It uses its special move Sticky Net to
shoot viscous webs that bind the enemy.

A Vegetation Digimon resembling a great withered 
tree. Made of normal wood, Woodmon catches 
Digimon that pass by and absorbs their energy to
survive. It can also use its root-like limbs to move. 
Brutal by nature, it attacks without rest when
angered. Woodmon's sturdy wooden trunk boasts 
high defense, but it's extremely weak against flame 
and particularly Fire Digimon such as Meramon 
and Birdramon. It uses its special move Branch 
Drain to extend its branch-like appendages, pierce
the opponent and absorb its energy.

A Digimon resembling an "oni," an ogre of Japanese 
folklore. The attacks from Ogremon's frighteningly
well-developed muscles bring tremendous destructive
power to bear. Extremely intelligent but just as
temperamental, this rage-driven being wreaks all
the havoc it can. Belligerent to a fault, it will boldly
challenge even opponents with significantly higher
battle strength compared to its own, and this has
earned it the moniker of the "Digimon Hunter."
The bone club Ogremon wields in its right hand
was earned from defeating SkullGreymon in battle.
It unleashes its special move Pummel Whack by
swinging its massive arms.

A Mysterious Beast Digimon in the shape of a giant
fox with nine tails. Kyubimon is feared as a beast
that brings destruction and decay, but in ancient
times it was hailed as a bringer of peace. A  Renamon
with particularly strong abilities and a wide range of
experience is said to Digivolve into a Kyubimon.
This Digimon lacks attack power, but possesses
incredible spiritual energy and specializes in spells.
The blue flames burning on its four limbs apparently
allow Kyubimon to gallop through the heavens.
Its signature move Fox Tail Inferno creates and
controls will-o'-the-wisps.

A savage Beast Dragon Digimon possessing the 
temperament of both beast and dragon, this 
heavyweight creature makes most Digimon flee at 
the mere sight of its shadow. Dorugamon can be 
ferocious like a wild beast in battle, but the dragon 
intelligence at its disposal means it's usually quite 
docile. Because of the antiquated interface on its 
forehead, this Digimon is presumed to be the 
Digivolution of an experimental "Prototype Digimon."
Dorugamon uses the special move Power Metal
to shoot a large iron ball from its mouth and crush
its foe.

A mythical Ancient Digimon that, even in the vast 
expanse of the Digital World, is said to have only
existed on the Folder Continent. Veedramon is 
extremely valuable to Digimon Tamers and rarely 
encountered, even on the Folder Continent. It's said
that only one Tamer has ever been able to win this 
Digimon over. Other than the V-shaped mark on its
chest, for which it's named, not much is known
about Veedramon or its surrounding ecosystem. It's 
sometimes mistaken for a dog for some reason. It
has extraordinary attacking power for a Champion
Digimon, exhibiting strength even outstripping that
of an Ultimate when the chips are down. It uses its
special move V-Nova Blast to shoot out a
high-temperature heat ray from its mouth.

A guardian of time that governs computer timers. 
Clockmon manages all "time" and "space" on
computers and across the Net, and can move time
forward and backward freely between the years 
1900 and 1999. It always maintains a neutral 
stance due to this incredibly dangerous and
terrifying ability, refusing to take part in conflict 
between Vaccine and Virus Digimon. Many think 
that if Clockmon were to lean toward either side 
of this equilibrium, the Digital World itself would 
collapse. It uses its special move Chrono Breaker 
to destroy the very time that flows in the enemy's 
body.

An Amphibian Digimon that mesmerizes those around
it with a cry altogether too pleasant for its strange
appearance. The chords Gekomon plays with the
three holes at the end of its tongue and the
improvisations created on the horn wrapped around
its neck can control its opponent's feelings. Rumor
has it that it's born when a hit song is created in
composition software, making Gekomon a kind of 
status symbol among musicians the world over. Its 
special move Symphony Crusher destroys the enemy's
insides with ultra-high frequency vibrations.

A Dragon Man Digimon DNA Digivolved from an 
ExVeemon and a Stingmon. It retains many 
elements of Dragon types, with the power of a
dragon and the iron-wall defense of an insect's 
carapace. More than just powerful, Paildramon also 
uses quick and agile moves to finish off opponents. 
It's very loyal, and will unquestioningly lay down its 
life for its master. Paildramon uses its special move 
Death Parade Blaster to fire an energy wave from 
two biological cannons extending from its waist.

Machinedramon, a Digimon made from the parts of 
countless Cyborg Digimon, possesses unimaginable
powers, and as such was apparently considered a 
successful experiment. Chaosdramon, with its 
crimson metal body, is an even more advanced
version of Machinedramon. Its frame is made from 
Red Digizoid, a rare metal made by re-refining the 
virtual super-metal Chrondigizoid to increase its 
hardness. As a result, it's capable of repelling all 
manner of attacks, and destroying absolutely
anything. Its special move Hyper Infinity Cannon 
fires super-dreadnought class energy blasts from 
both of its cannons.

A brand new type of Digimon. Three feelers grow 
from the top of its gelatinous, red body. Punimon is
incapable of fighting, instead relying on Acid Bubbles
to threaten enemies.

A small Digimon with a single horn on its head, formed
by hardening one of Punimon's feelers. Having
Digivolved to be more animalistic than Punimon,
Tsunomon is covered in soft fur. Filled with a playful
spirit, Tsunomon loves to pull pranks, and has yet to
develop its instinct for conflict.

A one-eyed Dragon Man Digimon with an abnormally 
developed right arm. Once a brawny dragon warrior, 
Cyclonemon had its right eye crushed by the warrior 
Leomon, transforming it into a demon of revenge. 
It strengthens and grows its arm larger in order to 
defeat Leomon, and hunts for a chance at retribution.
Shedding its pride as a warrior, Cyclonemon is now
a maddened combatant who thinks only of slaughter,
all for the sake of revenge. Its special move is
Hyper Heat, which melts any and all things.

An Android Digimon that guards the mysterious Royal
Base, a secret floating honey base. The antennae 
on Waspmon's head have excellent scouting 
capabilities, and it constantly patrols in search of
Digimon approaching the base, attacking any who 
even draw near. The propellers on its shoulders and
stabilizer on its back let it move rapidly in all 
directions as it defends against approaching foes,
driving them off with its powerful laser cannon. 
Waspmon's special move is Turbo Stinger, which 
fires its large-caliber laser cannon in a rapid burst.

A Crustacean Digimon formed when a Numemon is 
smart enough to search out a shell to protect itself. 
This makes ShellNumemon slightly more intelligent 
than Numemon, but also much more skittish, causing
it to flee into its shell at the slightest provocation.
Its defense increases dramatically while inside its
shell, allowing it to withstand kicks, stomps and the
like. Its special move is Mature Poop, by which it
hurls gobs of poop it's accumulated in its shell.

A Mutant Digimon with a gun barrel for a body.
Though the particulars of its genesis are completely
unknown, Deputymon's sense of justice makes it an 
active member of the Virus Busters, special Digimon
among Vaccine-attribute types with the ability to
eradicate and delete the "evil" will of Virus Digimon. It
also loves gambling—especially Russian roulette—and
its fairness is beyond reproach, allowing even Virus 
Digimon to get away if they win at this game. 
Deputymon's special move is Justice Bullet, which 
transforms Deputymon itself into a gun that unleashes 
a justice-imbued round.

Dracmon is the Dark Area's biggest prankster. It
won't hesitate to risk life and limb if that means
successfully pulling off a prank. One time, for
instance, it nearly died when it decided to try to
draw doodles on the faces of all Four Sovereign
Digimon (whether it succeeded or not is unclear).
While technically a vampiric Digimon, rumor has
it that lately it's been so absorbed in pulling a
prank on the Royal Knights that it's forgotten all
about drinking blood. It's also said that anyone
that looks directly into the Eye of Nightmares
cast from the evil eyes on its palms are subject
to its mind control.

A Mini Dragon Digimon incapable of flight, despite
the bat-like wings on both arms. Monodramon's
personality is rather rough—bordering on brutal,
and it gives the impression of a Digimon that enjoys
a good scrap. It's often found in the middle of most
Digital World brawls, causing even the likes of Ogremon
to get fed up with its persistence. Monodramon's
special move is Knuckle Beater, charging into the
enemy with staggering force before unleashing
its powerful claws in a straightforward strike.

A Vehicle-species Digimon similar to Mekanorimon, 
capable of leisurely flights through the sky. 
Blimpmon's soft balloon parts are protected by a
metal coating, but it appears to still be under 
development, as its left flank remains exposed.
Its signature move is Zeppelin Explosion, where it
fires cannonballs from the two cannons on top.

A Lesser Digimon that can run extremely fast, but 
only in a straight line. Dorimon hate to be tamed, so
many remain feral. Approaching it is dangerous, as 
it will charge in recklessly for a tackle. Dorimon's 
pointed ears are tough, acting as horns and inflicting
a modicum of damage when it tackles. That being 
said, it can't turn once it has gained enough speed. 
Dorimon's special move is Metal Drop, spitting metal
beads as it charges toward the enemy.

A Dragon Man Digimon resembling a humanoid 
lizard. Dinohyumon lives in an untamed land where 
every member of its fierce battle dragon tribe has
the makings of a warrior. Its burly muscles allow it
to swing its greatsword "Akinakes" with ease.
Dinohyumon's special move is Lizard Dance, which 
employs dance-like movements to cleave through 
foes with Akinakes and the blades on its arms.

A Bulb Digimon with a big flower blooming on its head.
Yokomon moves by deftly manipulating its root-like
tentacles, and is able to float softly through the air,
albeit for short distances. A curious creature,
its restless movements are delightful to behold.
Yokomon tend to live in groups—from dozens to
hundreds.

A Bulb Digimon with what appears to be a seedling
sprouting from its head. Tanemon Digivolved from a
Yuramon that landed on the ground after drifting 
through the air in search of the perfect environment.
Extremely skittish, it will use its four legs to quickly 
dig a hole so it can hide its body at the first sign of 
a threat. While Tanemon's body is hidden underground,
the seedling on its head makes it indistinguishable
from a plant, protecting it from harm. That being said,
this tactic proves ineffective against herbivorous
Digimon.

Despite resembling an aquatic dinosaur infant, this 
playful Digimon can move as skillfully as a seahorse.
Bukamon is quick to flee when others draw near, 
however. Its skin still isn't fit for the high pressure 
and low temperature of ocean depths, so it can 
only spend limited amounts of time submerged in 
the deep.

A small Digimon with feline traits. Fickle by nature,
Nyaromon has quite catlike behavior. While curious
and capricious in equal measure, it has a lonely side
as well. Nyaromon uses its special move Fox Tail to
whip the enemy with the wiry hairs on its tail.
However, not a single foe has ever been seen flinching
under this attack.

A Mythical Beast Digimon based on mythical creatures 
of legend, with the wings of Pegasus and the horn of 
a unicorn. It travels across the Net in the blink of an 
eye with the large wings on its back, and stabs foes 
with the sharp horn on its forehead. A "wild" Unimon 
is as hot-blooded as any untamed horse, but once 
trained, the Tamer can handle it with ease. Its special 
move is Holy Shot, which belches an energy bomb 
from its large mouth.

A Mammal Digimon with a strong sense of curiosity
and a love of mischief that it retained after its
Digivolution from Tsunomon. Elecmon fans out its
nine tails like a peacock in order to intimidate foes in
battle. Its special move is Sparkling Thunder.

A small Digimon that can perform low-altitude flight 
with the ear-like appendages on its head. Pagumon 
can use these ears deftly like hands, often pulling 
down its enemy's eyelids or slapping their rear with
them mockingly. Particularly mean-spirited, it can 
often be seen teasing the likes of Koromon or
Tsunomon, chasing them around and around. 
Pagumon may even spit Poison Bubbles from its 
mouth to bully other Digimon.

A Mammal Digimon with huge, sharp claws.
Gazimon is bipedal, an unusual trait for Mammal
types. The claws on its front limbs may have
developed while it used them like arms, causing
Gazimon to rely on its hind legs for ambulation.
Despite its small stature, this Digimon has an
exceedingly wild temperament, and never even
attempts to get along with humans. The claws
on Gazimon's forelimbs are extremely effective for
attacking, but are also surprisingly well-suited to
digging holes. Due to its mischievous nature, it
enjoys making pitfalls for other Digimon to fall
into. Gazimon's special move is Electric Stun Blast,
which belches out a poisonous gas.

A Baby Bird Digimon Digivolved from samurai-related
data. Hyokomon trains tirelessly to master the way of
the sword and is also developing a secret technique.
When it comes to swordsmanship, it talks the talk,
but doesn't quite walk the walk yet. The next
Digivolution of Hyokomon will only happen when it
breaks out of its shell through endless sword training.
Its special move is Downward Cleave, utilizing its wings
and leg strength to jump up and swing its sword straight
down to split its foe in two.

A Bird Man Digimon Digivolved through continuous
training with the sword. This led to acquiring mastery
over wielding two blades. Buraimon roams the
Digital World to continue its training and also
serves as a bodyguard, relying on its honed skills.
Seemingly willing to take on any job for a reward,
it's often treated as a thug. In reality, it's a gentle
soul that never takes a job that hurts the weak.
Buraimon's special move is Dual Swallow Reversal,
a cross slash performed quickly with two swords to
slice down a foe.

A Goblimon whose duty it is to hear the will of the
gods and convey it to its clan. Shamamon conducts
a ritual in which it performs a strange dance, and
supposedly hears divine messages once its fervor
reaches its peak. Shamamon's clan uses this ritual to
foretell matters of import. Shamamon uses its special
move Shama Hammer to bonk the enemy on the head
with the large club it also uses in its ritual.

A Goblimon raised in cold, snowy countries.
SnowGoblimon wears a warm hat and vest, so
cold places are no problem for it, and the skin on
the soles of its feet is thick enough to let it traipse
over snow without issue. SnowGoblimon's special
move is Snow Goblin Volt, which bats rock-filled
snowballs at its foe with all the fervor of a demon.

A Digimon resembling an "oni," an ogre of Japanese 
folklore. Fugamon is from the same clan as Ogremon, 
and shares its wild, battle-loving nature. Attacks 
unleashed from this Digimon's tremendous muscles 
hold terrible power, causing unadulterated destruction.
Fugamon's special move is Evil Hurricane, which
mows down everything with a swing of its bone club.

A species of Ogremon that lives in cold regions. 
Hyogamon is extremely territorial, flying off the handle
and attacking anyone who takes even a step inside its 
domain (even getting into occasional clashes with 
Mojyamon over territory). Its special move is Snow 
Punch, which unleashes a chilling blow.

A larval Digimon whose epidermis has yet to
solidify due to it living underwater. Otamamon
swims through swamps and rivers upstream of the
Net Ocean using its large tail, occasionally
clambering onto rocks with its developed forelimbs
to do vocal exercises. Unlike those of an average
organism, its hind legs are almost completely
undeveloped, acting as rudders in the stead of its
propulsive tail. Unlike other Rookies, this Digimon's
future Digivolution seems quite promising, but it's
extremely prone to mutation, so caution is
warranted when raising it. Otamamon's special
move is Lullaby Bubble, which sends opponents
into an eternal slumber.

A brutal Insectoid Digimon with massive wings. These 
wings allow Flymon to skirt through the air at ultrahigh 
speeds, creating sonic booms called "Howling Noise" 
in its wake that rob unlucky victims of their hearing. 
Its body is protected by a tough carapace, and it 
pinches foes with its huge talons before killing them 
with the extra-potent venomous stinger on its tail. The
Digivolution process of Insectoid Digimon is still 
unknown, but from its face, some have surmised that
Flymon originally Digivolved from a Kunemon-type 
creature. Its special move is Brown Stingers, which 
shoots a stinger from its tail that completely paralyzes 
the Digimon it pierces, turning it purple before ending 
its life. Incidentally, this nasty stinger can be regrown 
over and over again.

An Undead Digimon whose muscles have rotted off. 
Raremon tried to prolong its life by mechanizing itself, 
but the process was unstable, causing the data 
composing its body to start falling apart. Even so, its 
machine parts grant this creature life, preventing its 
death and allowing it to survive in this awful state.
This crumbling form affords neither attack power nor 
intelligence, making Raremon act according to instinct
alone. Its body emits a stench awful enough to send 
In-Training Digimon running, and it won't fight
anything below Champion level.

A cursed Digimon in the shape of a spider, whose 
entire body is infested with a computer virus. Even 
though a Spider-species type, Dokugumon was
originally a gentle and quiet Insectoid Digimon. 
One day, however, it was caught in a powerful
electromagnetic storm, and was infected with a 
computer virus that had been lurking around the Net. 
From that moment on, it became one big lump of 
venom—in other words, a nasty computer virus, 
corroding everything it touched. Dokugumon's 
eight-legged mobility is worthy of special mention, 
too. Even if the enemy runs from it at full speed, this 
Digimon will be right on its heels, pursuing it until it 
tires itself out. And then, as soon as it stops to take a
rest, Dokugumon uses Venom Blast on it, unleashing 
a dreadful, venomous attack from its fiendish fangs.

A Sea Animal Digimon with fins on its feet with which
to paddle through water. Gizamon is more suited to
life underwater than on land, using its fins and strong
hind legs to swim quickly through aquatic areas.
On land, however, it bounces around like a frog.
Gizamon acts cowardly on land, but displays a
ferocious disposition once back in the water. Its
special move is Spiral Edge, which attacks foes with
its sharp-edged dorsal fins.

An Ore Digimon with powerful defensive abilities,
having armored itself using ore data from its
surroundings. As spunky, mischievous and ambitious
as any young tough guy, Gotsumon leads around
groups of low-generation Digimon as it travels the
system. It also has a selfish side,and can be a real
handful when angered, rampaging like an erupting
volcano. The ore data Gotsumon uses for its armor
differs depending on where and how it was generated,
giving Gotsumon the potential to Digivolve into a
number of different forms. Gotsumon's special
move is Rock Fist, which shoots extremely hard rocks
from its head.

An experimental Digimon built in a laboratory as a 
Virus Hunter. Made of praying mantis data, Snimon 
chases after its target with machine-like precision. 
Its cold personality makes it feared by both Vaccine
and Data-attribute types alike. The scythes on
Snimon's arms are sharpened to points, allowing 
this Digimon to cleave cleanly through anything. It 
has no eyes, but the red feelers on its head act as 
sensors to accurately track the target's position. 
Snimon's special move is Shadow Sickle, which 
unleashes a supersonic slash invisible to the naked 
eye.

A super heavy Dinosaur Digimon with giant horns 
growing from its shoulders. Tuskmon's foolhardy
personality means it will charge at and destroy every 
obstacle in its path, earning it the nickname of the
"Panzer Digimon." Specializing in charging tackles, 
Tuskmon has made countless Digimon fall before its
attacks. The stars on its arms represent the number 
of Digimon that Tuskmon has defeated (one hundred 
per star). If its horns break, it can shed them like 
shark teeth and bring new horns from the back to the 
front, making any attempt to destroy its horns fruitless.
Tuskmon's special move is Slamming Tusk, which
unleashes a super dreadnought-class punch.
