A Digimon resembling a witch, who pursued its rival,
Wizardmon, from Witchelny, the Digital World of
another dimension. Witchmon mastered the magics
of wind and water (advanced programming languages)
in its home dimension Witchelny, but then pursued 
Wizardmon to the Digital World and now trains 
vigorously in order to get a leg up on this rival that
aims to become a great mage. Witchmon has a bit of 
a cruel streak, more than a bit of pride and loathes
both convention and established routines.
Witchmon's special move is Baluluna Gale, which
unleashes a cutting wind imbued with magic power.

A small Vegetation Digimon in the shape of a
poisonous mushroom. Tiny but potent poisonous
mushroom bombs growing from Mushroomon's
body cause all kinds of afflictions. Anyone hit by
one of these bombs could start laughing
uncontrollably, have their body go numb, lose
their memory, or worse. Mushroomon is extremely
ill-tempered and enjoys picking on the weak, but
also has a shy side, always hiding half of its face.
Its special move is Fungus Crusher, scattering
multiple mini-mushroom bombs at once.

An extremely rare insect Machine Digimon that
was recently discovered. No insect Machine
Digimon had been discovered up to that point, and
so Kokuwamon's existence wasn't even considered
a possibility. Its stun gun-shaped head and arms
can discharge 100 megavolts of electricity when it
senses danger, so none can approach without
caution. Even so, Kokuwamon lacks any aggression,
sporting instead an accommodating nature that
seeks peace. Kokuwamon obtains nourishment
from electricity, and recharges itself with the two
limbs on its midsection. Its special move is
Mini Scissor Claw, which electrifies its pincers
to slice through even the sturdiest of objects.

A mysterious Ancient Digimon said to have been 
hunted to extinction due to the proliferation of the 
Internet. The wings of this Bird Digimon have
completely degenerated, preventing it from taking 
flight. Kiwimon also bears some aspects of a 
Vegetation Digimon, with leaf-like objects growing
from its head that it uses to absorb nutrients through
photosynthesis. It has no way to defend itself aside 
from the hard shell covering its head, and its docile 
personality makes it an easy target. Kiwimon's special 
move is Pummel Peck, attacking with the ChibiKiwimon 
hidden in its body. The beaks of the ChibiKiwimon are 
just as hard as Kiwimon's, and they explode when 
struck. Even if this explosion chars them to a crisp,
ChibiKiwimon will always bounce back.

A rare Digimon that, like Palmon, Digivolved in
reptilian fashion but is classified as a Vegetation
Digimon. The entirety of Floramon's face is shaped
like a flower, and it generally uses this petal-like
shell like a helmet to protect its head. When no
predators are around, or when in a good mood, it
will spread open the petals on its head and arms.
Floramon sees Palmon as a rival, and has a very
high opinion of itself. Its special move is Rain of
Pollen, which releases clouds of allergy-inducing 
pollen from the flowers on its arms. Anyone hit by
this attack—even a large Digimon—will be robbed
of both their composure and will to fight.

A power suit Digimon used by other, small-sized 
Digimon, making it the first Vehicle-species Digimon 
in the Digital World. Mekanorimon is unique in that 
it can't operate itself, and fails to function unless 
piloted by other Digimon. Given its Virus attribute, 
the Digimon controlling it can also be considered a
Virus Digimon. Mekanorimon is still in development,
meaning its DigiCore will overheat if it's used too 
much. Its special move is Twinkle Beam, which fires 
a beam from the linear lens embedded in its torso.
Any enemy hit by this beam loses control of their
body.

An Android Digimon resembling a tank. Known as the 
"Mercenary Digimon," Tankmon will back up Vaccine 
and Virus Digimon alike if there's profit to be made. 
It pulverizes incoming enemies to dust with its 
heavyweight power and the heavy ordnance covering
its body. A conflict enthusiast, Tankmon heads in the 
direction of any strife that pops up. Wherever this
lone wolf goes, conflict is sure to continue unceasingly.
Tankmon's special move is Hyper Cannon, which
launches a super-powerful missile from the gun
barrel on its head.

A Bird Digimon resembling a penguin found in the
computer of an Antarctic base. Since Penmon lives
in snow-covered regions, it doesn't do well in the
heat. It does quite well with humans, conversely,
and will happily waddle along behind them. Penmon's
wings have degenerated, so it can't fly or walk
very quickly. But when it slides across the ice on
its belly, it can reach speeds close to 40 mph.
When in the water, Penmon can use its small
wings to skillfully swim around. Its special move
is Super Slap, where it sneaks up on the enemy
to smack their cheeks as hard as it can with
both arms.

A flightless Bird Digimon that's the spitting image
of Penmon. Raised in tropical lands to the south,
Muchomon lives a life of constant cheer. It overflows
with passion, dances to a samba beat and loves its
vivid, richly-colored pelt. Muchomon's special move
is Tropical Beak, pecking the opponent with its
colorful beak.

Keramon is a Rookie Digimon that Digivolved from
Tsumemon. Now that its body has grown larger and
its mouth is bigger, it can devour more data.
Keramon is capable of consuming more than 100
megabytes per second, and most data is destroyed
the instant Keramon accesses it. Extremely playful
by nature, it thinks of its destructive acts as a kind
of game. Its special move is Crazy Giggle, with which
it unleashes a highly destructive beam of light from
its mouth as it laughs—if you can call it laughing.

Kuramon is an Unidentified Digimon that suddenly 
appeared on a computer network. A single Digi-Egg 
was born from the malice of humans abusing computers
and the aggression from conflicts unfolding over
networks. The Digi-Egg was the amalgamation of
humanity's destructive instincts, and the mysterious
Digimon born from it is incredibly dangerous. It
multiplies within a computer network like a virus,
causing minor network failures. Kuramon uses its
special move Glare Eye to produce a frothy substance
from its giant eye.

Kurisarimon is a Champion Digimon that resembles a
chrysalis. In order to Digivolve into a more powerful
form, the Rookie Keramon temporarily enters a
chrysalis state to store up its energy. As a result, it
becomes completely unable to move, but its tough
outer hide protects it while the tentacles that grow
from its back allow it to attack foes. Keramon can
sometimes Digivolve directly into an Ultimate Digimon
without going through this Champion phase, but
Digivolving into Kurisarimon allows it to reach a
more powerful Ultimate form. Its special move Data
Crusher involves using the tentacles that extend from
its back to destroy an enemy's composition data.

An In-Training Digimon that Digivolved beyond
Kuramon. The tips of its feelers are shaped like
talons, increasing its ferocity. Tsumemon corrodes 
data at frightening speed, causing networks to
malfunction. Its movement speed is just as fast,
making this Digimon difficult to catch once it's
Digivolved to this level. It uses its special move
Nail Scratch to rake the enemy with the talons on
its feelers.

A ferocious Digimon with amazing vigor and extreme
aggression. Even so, it's friendly to allies, and those
recognized by Shoutmon can establish a deep bond
that transcends species. Because passion is the
source of its strength, Shoutmon won't abandon
a battle no matter how much damage it receives,
contributing to its savage reputation.

A Mini Dragon Digimon with a cool white sheen.
Unfettered and hating shackles, Huckmon's
swashbuckling way of life is likely due to the
influence of Gankoomon's DNA. It faces the harsh
trials imposed by Gankoomon with composure.
Huckmon's lineage gives it a keen sense for battle,
and training supervised by the Sistermon siblings
makes it more than evenly matched in fights
against even Ultimate foes. Huckmon specializes
in nimble melee combat, using Fifth Rush to cleave
the opponent with its tough claws. It pursues its
dream to become a Royal Knight like Gankoomon.

Zubamon is one of the Legend-Arms that can transform
its body into a weapon. The fabled Legend-Arms are
said to be capable of either saving the world in the
hands of an angel, or destroying it in the hands of a
devil. Zubamon possesses the data of the Twentiest,
and often shouts "I am the Twentiest!" without knowing
what that means. It dislikes anything warped or twisted,
and is in constant pursuit of its ideal of sharpness.
In battle and in jest, it's always trying to look sharp, and
days when it succeeds put it in a good mood. Though it
has its Twenty Dive attack that involves rushing headlong
at an enemy, Zubamon's true strength lies in its weapon
form.

"I am the Twentiest! I won't stop! I'll keep on 
running!" With those words emblazoned on its soul, 
Zubamon Digivolved to ZubaEagermon. Its new form 
perfectly embodies that spirit, and ZubaEagermon is 
committed to constantly forging ahead, over good
terrain and bad, even if it's reduced to a crawl. Its 
special move is Vantheon, with which it curls up into
a ball and spins, slicing through enemies with the 
blade on its tail. In its sword form, which it's quite
proud of, it cuts its way through any foe with all of
its strength.

An enigmatic Digimon with a massive horn growing
from its head. While Terriermon's composition is 
enough to deem it a Beast Digimon, the form it
takes after Digivolving is still unknown. Rumor has
it that it's sometimes born with a twin. Terriermon's
extreme cuteness and calm behavior don't give the
impression that this Digimon is of the Combat Species.
Still, the power it exhibits in battle belies its
appearance. It uses its signature move Terrier Tornado
to spin both of its ears like a propeller, creating a
small tornado.

A Bird Digimon with powerful legs that runs faster 
than it can fly. Peckmon uses its special move Kunai
Wing to hurl steel feathers it keeps under its wings.

A Bird Digimon with more developed wings that
allow it to fly. In spite of this, Falcomon seems
obsessed with appearing from out of the sky riding
a giant kite like a ninja. Its special move is Ninja
Blade, which involves firing off cross-shaped
throwing stars made from its hardened feathers.

A calm, collected and extremely courteous Bird
Digimon. Just like Veemon, it's a descendant of a
unique species that prospered in ancient times,
and can borrow the power of the Digi-Eggs for
armored pseudo-Digivolution. Hawkmon uses its
special move Feather Slash to throw the feather
ornament on its head like a boomerang.

A Mammal Digimon clad head-to-toe in a sturdy
carapace. It is easy-going and courteous, but it
sometimes pushes its luck. Armadillomon is a
descendant of the same ancient species as
Veemon, so it can perform a special Armor
Digivolution. It uses its special move Diamond
Shell to launch its curled-up body at the
enemy.

An unusual Digimon composed of blocks made from
a special plastic. ToyAgumon is said to be an imitation
of Agumon made by children playing on the
Internet. It's extremely cute. Unlike the bold and
fearless Agumon, ToyAgumon has a skittish side,
and its blocks fly apart when it's startled. Despite
this, it has a strong sense of justice that won't
allow for any sort of wrongdoing. It also adores
children, and loves to spend time interacting with
them on the Net. Its special move is Plastic Blaze.
with which it shoots out a toy missile shaped like
a flame. It's surprisingly powerful.

A Digimon shaped like a clam and surrounded by
a sturdy shell. Its highly developed shell protects
what looks like an In-Training Slime. This deceptive
Digimon uses its face to lure enemies in before
attacking them. Syakomon also boasts a high
defense when its shell is closed, repelling small
attacks with ease. Its special move Black Pearl
Blast fires jadeite formed in its body at the enemy.

A Beast Man Digimon that is Digivolved from 
Terriermon, it's a special Hunter Digimon. Faster 
than its appearance suggests, Gargomon brings 
down its foes with unparalleled accuracy and 
precision. Its powerful legs let it jump high into 
the air, at which point it spreads its ears to glide. 
Cheerful by nature, Gargomon may lose control 
once angered. It's obsessed with its beloved 
"D-VI'S 503xx" jeans. It uses its special move 
Dumdum Uppercut to get close to the enemy 
and thrust up from below with its Gatling Arm.

An Armored Dragon Digimon completely sheathed 
in hardened skin. Tough protuberances cover it all 
over, giving its charge attack incredible destructive 
power. Although as an herbivore it lacks ferocity,
Ankylomon displays a brave nature nevertheless. It 
uses its special move Tail Hammer to ferociously 
beat the enemy with the iron ball on the tip of its 
tail. Any Digimon hit by this technique has its entire
skeleton (or wireframe) utterly obliterated.

A Beast Man Digimon DNA Digivolved from Aquilamon
and Gatomon. Silphymon has tremendously strong
legs, and is said to be able to leap high into the sky.
Upon reaching these heights, it then spreads its arms
and sails through the air like a glider. Silphymon uses
the radar devices on its ears to gather information,
then visually processes this data for viewing on its
head-mounted display, allowing it to pinpoint an
enemy's location, day or night. It uses its special move
Top Gun to extend its arms to fire an energy bomb.

A Mutant Digimon DNA Digivolved from Ankylomon 
and Angemon. Shakkoumon has a shiny silver body 
with white wings, and according to one theory, it's
actually an Angel Digimon that descended from on 
high into the Ancient Digital World. Since it can
rotate its head and torso a full 360 degrees, it's 
capable of attacking in any direction. Some people 
find it frightening because its lack of expression 
makes it impossible to tell what it's thinking, but it 
has a warm and gentle personality. Its special move 
Disaster Blaster shoots destructive red laser beams 
from its eyes. These lasers are said to reach 
temperatures of over 180,000 degrees Fahrenheit
at their focal point.

A rare species of mechanical Machine Digimon.
Some researchers believe Solarmon to be a mutation
of Hagurumon, but the truth of the matter remains a
mystery. Because its DigiCore generates heat, its body
is hot enough to cause burns. Solarmon uses its special
move Shiny Ring to throw heat-emitting gears that scorch
the enemy.

A Mollusk Digimon of the same species as Numemon. 
Geremon lacks attack power but is unusually ferocious,
rushing at the opponent no matter who they are.
As expected, this obstinate creature gets taken out
quickly, but then immediately forgets about its
defeats. For this reason, it picks fights with formidable
foes over and over again. Geremon uses its special
move Hyper Smell to secrete a violent stench from its
body.

A Dark Angel Digimon with a heart as cold as ice. 
This is the form that a Devimon with the cruelest 
spirit takes after Digivolution. IceDevimon deceives 
its foes with its silver tongue, then envelops them in 
wings of ice to freeze them.

Lopmon is the Rookie Digivolution of one sibling
in a pair of extremely rare twin Digimon. Of the
two, Terriermon has one horn growing from its
head, while Lopmon has three. Their ecosystem is
steeped in mystery, and while their composition
is enough to deem them Beast Digimon, nothing
else is known about them. Terriermon has a
laid-back personality, albeit with a lot of energy,
while Lopmon has the opposite disposition, being
more of a lonely crybaby. Neither seem like
Digimon of the Combat Species, but they do show
unexpected power in battle. Lopmon's special
move Blazing Ice fires a blast of icy bullets.

A Digimon of glittering platinum, shaped like a piece 
of poop. PlatinumSukamon is a type of Sukamon
that has taken in rare metal data, giving it a gorgeous 
appearance but the same abilities as the original. 
It doesn't appear to have received any sort of 
power-up. PlatinumSukamon uses its special move 
Rare Metal Poop to hurl poop with a metallic sheen 
at the enemy.

A Mollusk Digimon that established its position as 
king of the dark trash data world. BlackKingNumemon
uses its special move Dark Pupil to fire a black beam
of light from its round eyes.

A companion of Wizardmon from the other-dimensional
Digital World of Witchelny. Sorcermon uses the magics
of light and ice (advanced programming languages), 
and also has the ability to heal wounds with the holy
power of prayer. Its special move is Crystal Cloud, with
which it summons storm clouds from a wand topped
with crystallized ice in order to cause a massive blizzard.

A Digimon with a body made of ice. Icemon's origins 
are currently being researched. Perhaps it Digivolved
from Gotsumon, or maybe it's some sort of mutation. 
Its special move Iceball Bomb involves throwing
ice-cold frozen bombs at foes.

A Digimon composed almost entirely of earth data. 
MudFrigimon is thought to be a mutant born from
a mutation of Frigimon. It's friendly by nature and
dislikes fighting, but when the chips are down, it
can demonstrate rarely-seen power. It uses its
special move Great Weight to put all of its weight
behind a haymaker punch.

Guarding a Chrondigizoit mine, Guardromon 
transformed itself to withstand merciless repeated 
raids by illegal miners. Guardromon (Gold)'s armor 
is said to be the result of taking in Chrondigizoit
dust data floating in the air. This armor is more 
durable than a normal Guardromon's, and its 
special move Destruction Grenade succeeds in
boasting slightly more output. On the other hand, 
Guardromon (Gold)'s armor is heavier, and this is 
the primary reason why its movements have dulled
overall.
